<subSubSection id="96BC651BB73028420804F48E3D71F40A" pageId="21" pageNumber="411" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="DE193690B73028420804F48E3D71F40A" blockId="21.[92,1299,1978,3073]" pageId="21" pageNumber="411">
<emphasis id="ECD2EA82B73028420804F48E3E99F484" bold="true" box="[94,455,2847,2876]" pageId="21" pageNumber="411">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. The Sierra de Perija White-fronted Capuchin has not been assessed on The IUCN Red List. Ciénagas del Catatumbo and Sierra de Perija national parks in Venezuela and Tama National Natural Park in Colombia are within its distribution.
</paragraph>
